rComments: Possibly the most disorganized poorly taught course I have ever taken. Pre-recorded lecture videos are useless, just teach yourself from the textbook. Assignments and quizzes are easy enough, midterms and final were okay. However, she decided randomly during the course to change the format of the midterms and final as it was given on the syllabus.
She doesnt explain the materials clearly and you cant reach her after class(she doesnt answer your emails). If you enjoy teaching yourself, take her.

If you would like to take her course, be prepared to read and do self-study. Her lecture was not helpful. The Midterm and Final have a lot of questions and many of them are harder than the exercises that she provides.

rComments: Prerecorded video lectures were useless. She doesn't make time to answer questions and does not respond to emails

please, PLEASE, avoid. And if you have to take this class with her. Forget her lectures and use the text instead. She does not explain the topics well and it is hard to learn from her as she speaks very quickly and does not answer questions or emails.

Idk about in class but online it was awful. One assignment, one quiz and a discussion board (with our group) EVERY WEEK. Her lectures were a waste of time, shed throw us in breakout rooms for something i could do on my own. Her last two exams were unrealistic, not enough time to actually do well. For your mental healths sake, i dont recommend.

She doesn't answer her emails. Completely disorganized. She nearly lost my ungraded quiz. Please, for your mental health's sake, pick another prof, because she'll drive you up the walls!
